<p style=";font:normal 1.8em 'Josefin Slab';color:#333;line-height:1.3em;"><span style="background-color:#EEE">ELLO, I'M DAVID.</span> As a graphic designer, I've worked with template-based products many times. By "template-based products", I'm talking invitations, place cards, greeting cards&hellip; <span style="background-color:#EEE;font-style:italic;">designs that stay the same but have elements that can be personalised</span>, such as the wording on an invitations or a colour scheme.</p>

<p style="font:normal 1.8em 'Josefin Slab';color:#333;line-height:1.3em;">Making changes to templates is a tedious job: clients would email me with changes, and then like a robot I'd do some cutting and pasting before emailing back a proof. I decided that for these simple tasks: changing colours, wording, or fonts, there had to be a more efficient way&hellip;<span style=";background-color:#EEE;font-style:italic;">Wouldn't it be better if clients could cut me out of the equation and change these elements themselves?</span> </p>

<p style=";font:normal 1.8em 'Josefin Slab';color:#555;line-height:1.4em;">I'd seen Web sites online that allowed you to manipulate existing templates, but they all seemed very slow: lots of page reloads and spinning icons each time you made a change. It got me thinking about one of the simplest products you can create as a designer&mdash;place cards&mdash;and I started to imagine the sort of software that would make creating place cards easier. It would:

<ul><li>
  Allow you to copy and paste an entire list of guest names in one go</li>
  
  <li style="background-color:white">Edit names quickly and easily</li>
  <li style="font-style:italic;">Change colour schemes very quickly and see the changes instantly</li>
  <li  style="background-color:white">Change the fonts of all the names in one go</li>
  <li style="font-style:italic;">Easily make fonts bigger or smaller on individual place cards when guest names are very long or very short (&ldquo;Alice&rdquo; on a place card needs to be in bigger text than &ldquo;Mrs Maureen Smithson-Jacobs&rdquo;)</li>
  <li style="background-color:white">Auto save everything as you work.</li>
  <li style="font-style:italic;">Do it all through a Web site from anywhere</li>
  <li style="background-color:white">Print straight from any browser in professional quality</li>
  <li style="font-style:italic;">Make it work on tablets and mobile phones as well</li>
</li></ul>
<p style="padding-top:1em;font:normal 1.8em 'Josefin Slab';color:#555;line-height:1.4em;">and most of all, it would work really fast!
</p>


